{
  "stem": "1282.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But what it really meant is that they formed-- as the Americans were approaching and they were constantly bombarding the railroads, they organized groups of 500 and trains that were constantly moving in every direction.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So when the railroads were bombed, it was very easy to find one these brigades, as they called it, which consisted of 500 people, German guards, and equipment to fix the railroads.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So this way they were able to maintain the railroads behind the line very quickly.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I wind up on one of those, several days later on one of those work camps.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It sounds good in a way, because I was able to work, and they gave us food, just enough for survival.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The problem was the following, that we never knew when they would take us and blow the whistle and we would have to start working.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Day and night, we were constantly-- we didn't know where we were.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We were never told where we were.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But the routine was the following, that when we stopped somewheres, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the Germans got out, set up the machine guns, and started screaming with their dogs, [GERMAN] out, out, out.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And what we did is, they opened up a cattle car.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We got out.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we started digging two foxholes alongside the railway.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We stopped behind [INAUDIBLE] or behind the bombed-out railroad.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But we dug foxholes all the way through, and under Germans watching us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Then we went back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the Germans went into the foxholes and set up machine guns facing the railroad tracks.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Second time we come out, they opened up the-- the places where they kept the equipment.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We had all the equipment to fix the railroads.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
